sbrk(0)         -> returns current program break
sbrk(4096)      -> extends heap by 4096 bytes, returns old break
brk(old + 8192) -> sets break to specific address

malloc(size):
  if size < 128KB:
    use sbrk to extend heap, carve block from it
  else:
    use mmap for a private anonymous mapping

free(ptr):
  if sbrk-allocated: add to free list (stays in process)
  if mmap-allocated: munmap (returns to OS immediately)

